pingouin.datasets.read_dataset

pingouin.datasets.read_dataset(dname)[source]

Read example datasets.

Parameters:
dname : string

Name of dataset to read (without extension). Must be a valid dataset present in pingouin.datasets
Returns:
data : pd.DataFrame

Dataset

Examples

Load the ANOVA dataset

>>> from pingouin.datasets import read_dataset
>>> df = read_dataset('anova')
